data.name: Krookodile-EX
rules: Pokémon-EX rule: When a Pokémon-EX has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Second Bite
attacks.text: This attack does 10 more damage for each damage counter on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Megaton Fang
attacks.text: Discard a card from your hand. If you can't discard a card, this attack does nothing.

data.name: Krookodile

attacks.name: Torment
attacks.text: Choose 1 of the Defending Pokémon's attacks. That Pokémon can't use that attack during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Krookoroll
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon already has any damage counters on it, this attack does 40 more damage.

data.flavorText: It can expand the focus of its eyes, enabling it to see objects in the far distance as if it were using binoculars.

data.name: Krookodile

attacks.name: Piston Headbutt
attacks.text: Move an Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

data.flavorText: Very violent Pokémon, they try to clamp down on anything that moves in front of their eyes.

data.name: Krookodile

abilities.name: Black Eyes
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon, you may flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Thrash
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage. If tails, this Pokémon does 20 damage to itself.

data.flavorText: They never allow prey to escape. Their jaws are so powerful, they can crush the body of an automobile.

data.name: Krookodile

attacks.name: Bother
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent can't play any Supporter cards from his or her hand during his or her next turn.

attacks.name: Knock Back
attacks.text: Your opponent switches his or her Active Pokémon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon.

data.flavorText: Very violent Pokémon, they try to clamp down on anything that moves in front of their eyes.

attacks.name: Dark Clamp
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Bombast
attacks.text: Does 40 damage times the number of Prize cards you have taken.

data.flavorText: They never allow prey to escape. Their jaws are so powerful, they can crush the body of an automobile.

data.name: Krookodile

attacks.name: False Accusation
attacks.text: This attack does 20 more damage for each card in your opponent's hand.

attacks.name: Obsidian Fang
attacks.text: Before doing damage, discard all Pokémon Tool cards from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

data.flavorText: Its unique faculty of sight can detect small prey more than 30 miles away, even in the midst of a sandstorm.

data.name: Krookodile

attacks.name: Dredge Up
attacks.text: Discard the top 3 cards of your opponent's deck.

attacks.name: Tantrum
attacks.text: This Pokémon is now Confused.

data.flavorText: It conceals itself in sandstorms that Flygon whip up and waits patiently for prey to appear.

data.name: Krookodile

attacks.name: Chomp Chomp Panic
attacks.text: This attack does 50 damage for each Colorless in your opponent's Active Pokémon's Retreat Cost.

attacks.name: Crunch
attacks.text: Discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

data.flavorText: When it spots prey, even at a distance of over 30 miles, it swims through the desert as if it were water, then jumps out and chomps them.

attacks.text: Does 40 damage times the number of Prize cards you have taken.

data.flavorText: This extremely rare Pokémon is a different color than usual. It is very hard to find.

abilities.name: Bully of the Sands
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may discard a random card from your opponent's hand. If this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon and is Knocked Out by damage from an opponent's attack, you may discard a random card from your opponent's hand.

attacks.name: Double-Edge
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

data.flavorText: This Pokémon is known as the Bully of the Sands. Krookodile's mighty jaws can bite through heavy plates of iron with almost no effort at all.

data.name: Krookodile

attacks.name: Chomp Chomp Bite
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. For each heads, discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Earthquake
attacks.text: This attack also does 30 damage to each of your Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

data.flavorText: After clamping down with its powerful jaws, it twists its body around to rip its prey in half.
